          <td class="px-3 py-3 text-center"><span class="text-teal-600 font-bold">&#10003;</span> <span class="text-slate-600">Within risk limits</span></td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="bg-slate-50">
          <td class="px-3 py-3 font-medium text-slate-600">Profit Split (Funded)</td>
          <td class="px-3 py-3 text-center font-semibold text-teal-600">80%</td>
          <td class="px-3 py-3 text-center font-semibold text-teal-600">80%</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="bg-white">
          <td class="px-3 py-3 font-medium text-slate-600">Account Scaling</td>
          <td class="px-3 py-3 text-center text-slate-900">Up to $500,000</td>
          <td class="px-3 py-3 text-center text-slate-900">Up to $500,000</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="bg-slate-50">
          <td class="px-3 py-3 font-medium text-slate-600">Best For</td>
          <td class="px-3 py-3 text-center text-slate-700 whitespace-normal">Faster path to funding</td>
          <td class="px-3 py-3 text-center text-slate-700 whitespace-normal">Gradual evaluation with more drawdown room</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>
  <p class="text-xs text-slate-500 -mt-8 mb-10">* 2-Step Step 2 max drawdown is 10% for $5k–$50k accounts, but 8% for $100k and $200k accounts.</p>

  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <!-- ONE STEP CHALLENGE                                              -->
  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <div class="mb-10">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3 flex items-center gap-2">
      <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-7 h-7 rounded-full bg-teal-500 text-white text-xs font-black flex items-center justify-center">1</span>
      One Step Challenge
    </h3>

    <p class="mb-3">
      In the one step challenge, you must reach a <strong>10% profit target</strong> while staying within a <strong>3% daily drawdown</strong> and <strong>6% maximum drawdown</strong>. There is only a single evaluation step, meaning once the profit target is hit and all rules are respected, the trader becomes eligible for a funded account. There is no maximum time limit, but a minimum of <strong>3 trading days</strong> is required. A <strong>45% consistency rule</strong> applies, and weekend holding is <strong>not allowed</strong>.
    </p>
    <p class="mb-4">
      Because there is no second step, the one step challenge offers a faster route to funding, but with tighter drawdown limits compared to the two step option. This structure suits traders who are confident in their execution and prefer to complete the evaluation in a single phase.
    </p>

    <div class="overflow-x-auto rounded-xl border border-slate-200 mb-5">
      <table class="w-full text-sm">
        <thead class="bg-slate-50 text-xs font-semibold text-slate-500 uppercase tracking-wide">
          <tr>
            <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left">Account Size</th>
            <th class="px-4 py-3 text-right">Fee (USD)</th>
            <th class="px-4 py-3 text-right">Max Daily Loss (3%)</th>
            <th class="px-4 py-3 text-right">Max Overall Loss (6%)</th>
            <th class="px-4 py-3 text-right">Profit Target (10%)</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody class="divide-y divide-slate-100">
          <tr class="bg-white">
            <td class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-slate-900">$10,000</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-slate-900">$154</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-slate-700">$300</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-slate-700">$600</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-slate-700">$1,000</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="bg-slate-50">
            <td class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-slate-900">$25,000</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-slate-900">$309</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-slate-700">$750</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-slate-700">$1,500</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-slate-700">$2,500</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="bg-white">
            <td class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-slate-900">$50,000</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-slate-900">$469</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-slate-700">$1,500</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-slate-700">$3,000</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-slate-700">$5,000</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="bg-slate-50">
            <td class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-slate-900">$100,000</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-slate-900">$809</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-slate-700">$3,000</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-slate-700">$6,000</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-slate-700">$10,000</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="bg-white">
            <td class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-slate-900">$200,000</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-slate-900">$1,495</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-slate-700">$6,000</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-slate-700">$12,000</td>
            <td class="px-4 py-3 text-right text-slate-700">$20,000</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <!-- TWO STEP CHALLENGE                                              -->
  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <div class="mb-10">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-900 mb-3 flex items-center gap-2">
      <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-7 h-7 rounded-full bg-teal-500 text-white text-xs font-black flex items-center justify-center">2</span>
      Two Step Challenge
    </h3>

    <p class="mb-3">
      The two step challenge requires traders to pass two consecutive steps &mdash; an <strong>Evaluation Phase</strong> followed by a <strong>Verification Phase</strong>. In Step 1, you must achieve a <strong>10% profit target</strong> with a <strong>4% daily drawdown</strong> and <strong>8% max drawdown</strong>. In Step 2, the profit target reduces to <strong>5%</strong>, daily drawdown increases to <strong>5%</strong>, and the max drawdown is <strong>10%</strong> for $5k&ndash;$50k accounts or <strong>8%</strong> for $100k&ndash;$200k accounts. Each step requires a minimum of <strong>3 trading days</strong>.
    </p>
    <p class="mb-3">
      Step 1 includes a <strong>soft 45% consistency rule</strong> &mdash; no single trading day should represent more than 45% of Step 1 profits. This does not automatically fail the account, but repeated or extreme deviations may trigger review.
    </p>
    <p class="mb-4">
      The two step challenge provides more drawdown room and allows <strong>weekend holding within risk limits</strong>, making it better suited for traders who prioritise capital preservation and consistency over speed.
    </p>

    <div class="overflow-x-auto rounded-xl border border-slate-200 mb-5">
      <table class="w-full text-sm">
        <thead class="bg-slate-50 text-xs font-semibold text-slate-500 uppercase tracking-wide">
          <tr>
            <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left">Account Size</th>
